{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.4",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 4,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 4 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:1",
      "text": "Hear, O sons, a father's instruction, and be attentive, that you may gain insight;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:2",
      "text": "for I give you good precepts: do not forsake my teaching.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:3",
      "text": "When I was a son with my father, tender, the only one in the sight of my mother,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:4",
      "text": "he taught me, and said to me, “Let your heart hold fast my words; keep my commandments, and live;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:5",
      "text": "do not forget, and do not turn away from the words of my mouth. Get wisdom; get insight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:6",
      "text": "Do not forsake her, and she will keep you; love her, and she will guard you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:7",
      "text": "The beginning of wisdom is this: Get wisdom, and whatever you get, get insight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:8",
      "text": "Prize her highly, and she will exalt you; she will honor you if you embrace her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:9",
      "text": "She will place on your head a fair garland; she will bestow on you a beautiful crown.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:10",
      "text": "Hear, my son, and accept my words, that the years of your life may be many.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:11",
      "text": "I have taught you the way of wisdom; I have led you in the paths of uprightness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:12",
      "text": "When you walk, your step will not be hampered; and if you run, you will not stumble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:13",
      "text": "Keep hold of instruction, do not let go; guard her, for she is your life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:14",
      "text": "Do not enter the path of the wicked, and do not walk in the way of evil men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:15",
      "text": "Avoid it; do not go on it; turn away from it and pass on.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:16",
      "text": "For they cannot sleep unless they have done wrong; they are robbed of sleep unless they have made some one stumble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:17",
      "text": "For they eat the bread of wickedness and drink the wine of violence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:18",
      "text": "But the path of the righteous is like the light of dawn, which shines brighter and brighter until full day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:19",
      "text": "The way of the wicked is like deep darkness; they do not know over what they stumble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:20",
      "text": "My son, be attentive to my words; incline your ear to my sayings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:21",
      "text": "Let them not escape from your sight; keep them within your heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:22",
      "text": "For they are life to him who finds them, and healing to all his flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:23",
      "text": "Keep your heart with all vigilance; for from it flow the springs of life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:24",
      "text": "Put away from you crooked speech, and put devious talk far from you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:25",
      "text": "Let your eyes look directly forward, and your gaze be straight before you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:26",
      "text": "Take heed to the path of your feet, then all your ways will be sure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.4.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 4:27",
      "text": "Do not swerve to the right or to the left; turn your foot away from evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
